{{Infobox journal | title = Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences | cover = | editor = [[Katherine H. Freeman]], [[Raymond Jeanloz]] | discipline = [[Earth science]], [[planetary science]] | abbreviation = Annu. Rev. Earth Planet. Sci. | publisher = [[Annual Reviews (publisher)|Annual Reviews]] | country = | frequency = Annually | history = 1973-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 10.188 | impact-year = 2013 | website = http://www.annualreviews.org/journal/earth | link1 =http://www.annualreviews.org/loi/earth | link1-name = Online access | JSTOR = | OCLC = 42635458 | LCCN = 72082137 | CODEN = AREPCI | ISSN = 1545-4495 | eISSN = 0084-6597 }} '''''Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences''''' is an annual [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] published by [[Annual Reviews (publisher)|Annual Reviews]], which broadly covers [[Earth science|Earth]] and [[planetary science]]s, including [[geology]], [[atmospheric sciences]], climate, [[geophysics]], [[environmental science]], geological hazards, [[geodynamics]], planet formation, and solar system origins. The [[editors-in-chief]] are [[Katherine H. Freeman]] ([[Pennsylvania State University]]) and [[Raymond Jeanloz]] ([[University of California, Berkeley]]).
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2013 [[impact factor]] of 10.188.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
