{{DEFAULTSORT:List of named storms (U-Z)}} [[Category:Lists of tropical cyclones|Names U]]

List of [[park]]s and [[garden]]s in the Free and Hanseatic City of [[Hamburg]].
Hamburg is one of Europe's greenest metropolises, with parks and gardens alone making up eight percent of the city's land area,<ref name="hamburg.de">{{cite web|title=Hamburger Parkanlagen|url=http://www.hamburg.de/parkanlagen/|website=hamburg.de|publisher=Free and Hanseatic City of Hamburg|language=German|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=laurustico>{{cite web|title=Parks und Gartenanlagen in Hamburg und Umgebung|url=http://www.laurustico.de/hamburg-park.html|website=laurustico.de|publisher=Laurustico, Club für Gartenfreunde|language=German|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref> in addition to even larger percentages for [[nature reserve]]s and agricultural land areas. In 2011, the city was voted "[[European Green Capital]]", in 2013 Hamburg hosted the [[Bundesgartenschau|International Garden Show]] (IGS) on the island of [[Wilhelmsburg, Hamburg|Wilhelmsburg]].
