rest school (learning style)|forest schools]] initiative "I Ur och Skur" (Rain or Shine) | Sweden |- | 2010 | Green investment management | The banks [[Merkur Andelskasse]], [[Ekobanken]], and [[Cultura Sparebank]] | Denmark, Sweden, and Norway |- | 2011 | [[Sustainable tourism]] | [[Scandic Hotels]] | Norway |- | 2012 | [[Biodiversity]] | [[Olli Manninen]] | Finland |- | 2013 | [[Resource efficiency]] | [[Selina Juul]] and the [[Stop Wasting Food]] movement | Denmark |- | 2014 | Environmental work by a Nordic town or community | City of [[Reykjavik]]<ref name="winner 2014" /> | Iceland |- | 2015 | Reduction of [[greenhouse gas]] emissions<ref name="winner 2015" /> | [[SEV (company)|SEV]] energy company<ref name="winner 2015">{{cite web|url=http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-natur-og-miljoepris/winner-of-the-nordic-council-nature-and-environment-prize-2015|title=Winner of the Nordic Council Nature and Environment Prize 2015|website=Nordic Council|access-date=19 October 2016}}</ref> | Faroe Islands |- | 2016 | Digital promotion of [[sustainable living]]<ref name="nominees 2016">{{cite web|url=http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-natur-og-miljoepris/nominations-for-the-nordic-council-environment-prize-2016|title=Nominations for the Nordic Council Environment Prize 2016|website=Nordic Council|access-date=19 October 2016}}</ref> | ''Too Good To Go'', an app that combats food waste by enabling users to buy surplus food from restaurants at affordable prices<ref name="winner 2016">{{cite web|title=Winner of the Nordic Council Environment Prize 2016|website=Nordic Council|access-date=1 November 2016|url=http://www.norden.org/en/nordic-council/nordic-council-prizes/nordisk-raads-natur-og-miljoepris/winner-of-the-nordic-council-environment-prize-2016}}</ref> | Denmark |- | 2017 | Iniatives that bring people closer to the waste-free society.<ref name="nominees 2017">{{cite web|url=https://www.norde