The '''Regulatory Authority for Energy''' (RAE or ΡΑΕ from Ρυθμιστική Αρχή Ενέργειας in [[Greek language|Greek]]) is an independent administrative authority, which was established in order to implement the provisions of Directive 96/92/EC for the liberalization of the electricity market in [[Greece]].<ref>http://www.rae.gr/site/en_US/categories_new/about_rae/intro.csp</ref>
RAE is a member of the [[Council of European Energy Regulators]]. <ref>http://www.ceer.eu/portal/page/portal/EER_HOME/EER_ABOUT/MEMBERS</ref>
